{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW BLOCK REMEDIATION (2026-07-13, /rebar-implement run). The epic + child 368c plan-reviews BLOCKed on genuine design underspecification. Resolved concretely (design intent unchanged; mechanics made executable + falsifiable):\n\nE2/T8 (config schema): trusted-env keys pinned in .rebar/trusted_environments.yaml (YAML, out-of-band on the Gerrit-gated code branch, NOT tickets branch). Schema: environments[].{env_id, keys[].{public_key(OpenSSH ed25519), added_at_commit, revoked_at_commit|null}}. Added 'Trust config & era-validity protocol' section + tightened AC2. Propagated to child 42d1.\n\nG6/T1 (broken era reuse): the identity epic's era mechanism resolves key add/revoke POSITIONS to commits by globbing tickets-branch event files (authorship.resolve_event_commit/_keyring_for). Env keys are out-of-band (NOT tickets branch), so that resolver CANNOT be reused verbatim. Resolution: config stores EXPLICIT git SHAs (added_at_commit/revoked_at_commit on main); we reuse the era-validity RULE (git merge-base --is-ancestor comparison + key_not_valid_at_era verdict), not the event resolver. The out-of-band security requirement (tickets branch is auto-pushed, not Gerrit-gated) FORCES this — it is not a live design fork. Propagated to child 368c AC3.\n\nG6 (368c verdict): key_not_valid_at_era is NOT emitted by the substrate era check (that returns unknown_principal); it is a TWO-PHASE reclassification in the gate-layer caller (verify_authorship.py): verify vs any historical key; if that passes but era-scoped check fails -> key_not_valid_at_era, else bad_signature. 368c AC3 now requires the op-cert verifier do the analogous two-phase check.\n\nF1 (effort-framed migration): AC6 reframed from 'documented migration' to a NAMED OBSERVABLE ARTIFACT docs/migrations/hmac-opcert-removal.md (test asserts exists/non-empty/names cutover). Propagated to child 8f1d.\n\nAdvisory findings (20 epic + 8 on 368c) reviewed; applied the ones that sharpen the plan (concrete file paths, verdict semantics). Re-running plan-review on epic + 368c to earn fresh attestations."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783969029214326001,"uuid":"0fd3bf89-7735-4eb0-a92b-3da3bc647439"}